Pin devcontainer build inputs for CI rebuilds

The devcontainer is rebuilt from scratch in CI, so every floating input
(debian:testing, the live apt archive, latest release downloads) made
consecutive builds diverge. Pin the base image by digest, freeze apt on
the matching snapshot.debian.org timestamp, and pin the previously
floating tool versions: Rust toolchain (via rust-toolchain.toml),
cargo-about, claude, codex, eksctl, aws-cli and node (with checksum
verification). Preloaded container images are pinned by digest since
tags like wolfi-base:latest and registry:2 move. The repo clone that
warms the cargo cache gets a RUMPELPOD_REF build arg so CI can pin the
commit under test.

Also fix the ECR credential helper download to use the arm64 build on
arm64 instead of unconditionally fetching amd64, and drop the
dockerfile syntax header: it pulled the floating docker/dockerfile:1.7
frontend image although no feature beyond the builtin frontend of any
BuildKit-era docker is used.
